  - CC-BY-4.0
keywords:
  - marine litter
  - river plastic
  - Lagrangian drifter
  - citizen science
  - open hardware
  - source-to-sea
  - FF-ID
abstract: >-
  A low-cost, recover-first, cellular GPS drifter (upcycled PET bottle + ESP32 + LTE Cat-1 + separate
  L76K GNSS) and an open, citable data standard (FF-ID) for mapping how floating trash travels from
  source to sea, so communities know where to place booms and cleanups. Firmware MIT, hardware
  CERN-OHL-S, docs CC BY-SA, data CC BY. Reference design — field validation and a DOI-deposited
  dataset are pending; all figures are estimates until bench + field measurement.
